This paper is primarily focused on video-based face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves learning ordinal filters and features, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep feature representations, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques to solve a non-convex integer program problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
